# lv_cpython_mod

Native CPython extension module `lvgl` (no MicroPython runtime). Use these docs:

- **[README.md](README.md)** — what it is, TestPyPI install, usage and API style
- **[BUILDING.md](BUILDING.md)** — clone, requirements, build from source (`pip install -e .` or `pip.exe`)
- **[PUBLISHING.md](PUBLISHING.md)** — sync from lv_bindings, releases, TestPyPI CI

## Build / test (quick)

### Unix (WSL) — use `.venv`

```bash
git submodule update --init lvgl
python3 -m venv .venv
.venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt
.venv/bin/pip install -e .    # rebuild after lvpy_runtime.c or generated/lvgl_python.c changes

.venv/bin/python -c "import lvgl as lv; lv.init(); lv.deinit(); print('ok')"
```

### Windows — **no venv**; use `pip.exe` / `python.exe` from WSL

```bash
pip.exe install -e "$(wslpath -w /path/to/lv_cpython_mod)"
python.exe -c "import lvgl as lv; lv.init(); lv.deinit(); print('ok')"
```

Requires MSVC Build Tools (python.org CPython). Do not use MinGW for this extension.

## Gotchas

- Editable install does **not** auto-recompile on import; rerun `pip install -e .` after C changes.
